ssnStatusMaximumSessions.name: ssnStatusMaximumSessions
ssnStatusMaximumSessions.description: The maximum number of sessions that can exist in the system.

sessionStatusTable.name: sessionStatusTable
sessionStatusTable.description: A list of session status entries.

sessionStatusEntry.name: sessionStatusEntry
sessionStatusEntry.description: An entry containing object variables to describe a session.

ssnStatusIndex.name: ssnStatusIndex
ssnStatusIndex.description: The index number for this session status entry. Its value ranges from 1 to 'ssnStatusMaximumSessions'.

ssnStatusValidFlag.name: ssnStatusValidFlag
ssnStatusValidFlag.description: Value indicates whether this entry contains valid information or not. Setting a valid(2) session to invalid(1) causes an effective session termination.

ssnStatusUserName.name: ssnStatusUserName
ssnStatusUserName.description: The name of the remote user. The null string is returned if entry is invalid. For a Radius DNIS authenticated session, value of User-Name provided in Radius reply will be used if no second tier authentication is involved.

ssnStatusUserIPAddress.name: ssnStatusUserIPAddress
ssnStatusUserIPAddress.description: The IP address of the remote user. The value 0.0.0.0 is returned if entry is invalid.

ssnStatusUserSubnetMask.name: ssnStatusUserSubnetMask
ssnStatusUserSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask of the remote user. The value 0.0.0.0 is returned if entry is invalid.

ssnStatusCurrentService.name: ssnStatusCurrentService
ssnStatusCurrentService.description: The current service provided to the remote user. The value none(1) is returned if entry is invalid OR if user dials into the terminal server and is in midst of a login sequence.

ssnStatusCallReferenceNum.name: ssnStatusCallReferenceNum
ssnStatusCallReferenceNum.description: A unique number identifying this session. The value 0 is returned if entry is invalid.

sessionActiveTable.name: sessionActiveTable
sessionActiveTable.description: A list of active session entries. This table is similar to sessionStatusTable with invalid entries screened out and indexed by ssnActiveCallReferenceNum. ssnActiveCallReferenceNum tracks ssnStatusCallReferenceNum of sessionStatusTable.

sessionActiveEntry.name: sessionActiveEntry
sessionActiveEntry.description: An entry containing object variables to describe an active session.

ssnActiveCallReferenceNum.name: ssnActiveCallReferenceNum
ssnActiveCallReferenceNum.description: A unique number identifying this active session. Refer to ssnStatusCallReferenceNum for more information.

ssnActiveIndex.name: ssnActiveIndex
ssnActiveIndex.description: The index number for this session status entry. Its value ranges from 1 to 'ssnStatusMaximumSessions'. Refer to ssnStatusIndex for more information.

ssnActiveValidFlag.name: ssnActiveValidFlag
ssnActiveValidFlag.description: All entries will be valid(2). Refer to ssnStatusValidFlag for more information. Setting a vaild(2) session as invalid(1) causes an effective session termination.

ssnActiveUserName.name: ssnActiveUserName
ssnActiveUserName.description: The name of the remote user. Refer to ssnStatusUserName for more information. For a Radius DNIS authenticated session, value of User-Name provided in Radius reply will be used if no second tier authentication is involved.

ssnActiveUserIPAddress.name: ssnActiveUserIPAddress
ssnActiveUserIPAddress.description: The IP address of the remote user. Refer to ssnStatusUserIPAddress for more information.

ssnActiveUserSubnetMask.name: ssnActiveUserSubnetMask
ssnActiveUserSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask of the remote user. Refer to ssnStatusUserSubnetMask for more information.

ssnActiveCurrentService.name: ssnActiveCurrentService
ssnActiveCurrentService.description: The current service provided to the remote user. The value none(1) is returned if entry is invalid OR if user dials into the terminal server and is in midst of a login sequence. Refer to ssnStatusCurrentService for more information.

ssnActiveIdleTime.name: ssnActiveIdleTime
ssnActiveIdleTime.description: The time current session has been idle. Valid only for sessions terminated on any of the host cards(i.e. dial up sessions), for others 0 is always reported. For non-TNT and non-Max platforms 0 is always reported.

mppActiveStatsTable.name: mppActiveStatsTable
mppActiveStatsTable.description: A list of active MPP session statistics with invalid entries screened out and indexed by mppStatsMpID.

mppActiveStatsEntry.name: mppActiveStatsEntry
mppActiveStatsEntry.description: An entry containing object variables to describe an active MPP session. The variables are those seen in the Dyn Stat area of the LCD display.

mppStatsMpID.name: mppStatsMpID
mppStatsMpID.description: The MpID number for this active MPP session entry.

mppStatsRemoteName.name: mppStatsRemoteName
mppStatsRemoteName.description: The name of the remote user.

mppStatsQuality.name: mppStatsQuality
mppStatsQuality.description: Line quality. N/A: No MPP sessions currenly active, Good: <%1 CRC errors, Fair: <%5 CRC errors, Marginal: <%10 CRC errors, Poor: %10 or > CRC errors

mppStatsBandwidth.name: mppStatsBandwidth
mppStatsBandwidth.description: Total bit rate (Kbps) for the MPP session.

mppStatsTotalChannels.name: mppStatsTotalChannels
mppStatsTotalChannels.description: The total number of channels associated with this MPP session.

mppStatsCLU.name: mppStatsCLU
mppStatsCLU.description: Current percentage of line utilization for transmitted packets during this MPP session.

mppStatsALU.name: mppStatsALU
mppStatsALU.description: Average percentage of line utilization for transmitted packets during this MPP session.

mppStatsStartingTimeStamp.name: mppStatsStartingTimeStamp
mppStatsStartingTimeStamp.description: The starting time for this MPP session in seconds since startup.
